and discuss the
data rich feature

00:00:23.450 --> 00:00:25.800
of large astronomical surveys.

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:29.230
John most recently discovered
the two most distant stars

00:00:29.230 --> 00:00:33.940
in our galaxy, over one
million light-years away.

00:00:33.940 --> 00:00:36.530
So in addition to
being a professor,

00:00:36.530 --> 00:00:38.910
John is a blogger at
"Sky and Telescope",

00:00:38.910 --> 00:00:41.800
a prominent magazine
for astronomers,

00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:44.310
